ess%2C%20rising%20crime%20and%20homelessness%20could%20make%20this%20year%20its%20last%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224030%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20pedestrian%20crosses%20a%20street%20in%20the%20Outer%20Sunset%20district%20by%20Ocean%20Beach%20on%20June%2026%2C%202023%20in%20San%20Francisco%2C%20California.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64dcb4604ef9f30019f7e9bc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222687%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3Enull%3Cp%3ELoren%20Elliott%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20owner%20of%20luxury%C2%A0San%20Francisco%20retailer%20Gump's%20warned%20that%20this%20holiday%20season%C2%A0%26quot%3Bmay%20be%20our%20last.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EJohn%20Chachas%20attributed%20this%20to%20rising%20crime%2C%20homelessness%2C%20drug%20use%2C%20and%20remote%20work.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20said%20San%20Francisco%20is%20%26quot%3Bunlivable%20for%20its%20residents%2C%20unsafe%20for%20our%20employees%2C%20and%20unwelcoming%20to%20visitors.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20owner%20of%20an%20upmarket%20San%20Francisco%20retailer%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgumps.com%2Fpages%2Fabout-us%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efirst%20opened%20in%201861%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20warned%20that%20rising%20crime%20and%20homelessness%20in%20the%20city%20means%20this%20could%20be%20its%20last%20year%20operating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohn%20Chachas%2C%20the%20owner%20and%20chairman%20of%20Gump's%2C%20which%20sells%20luxury%20home%20decor%20and%20fine%20jewelry%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20said%20that%20as%20the%20company%20prepares%20for%20the%20holiday%20season%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20fear%20this%20may%20be%20our%20last%20because%20of%20the%20profound%20erosion%20of%20this%20city's%20current%20conditions.%26quot%3B%20Gump's%20is%20located%20just%20off%20Union%20Square%20in%20downtown%20San%20Franc