's%20interference%20in%20this%20process%20to%20investigate%20the%20merits%20of%20his%20recent%20study%20constitutes%20institutional%20harassment%2C%20curtails%20academic%20freedom%2C%20and%20forces%20scholars%20to%20operate%20in%20an%20environment%20of%20fear%2C%26quot%3B%20professors%20of%20the%20Economics%20department%20said%20in%20an%20open%20letter%20to%20the%20university.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20condemn%20this%20in%20the%20strongest%20terms%20and%20refuse%20as%20a%20collective%20to%20cooperate%20in%20any%20future%20attempt%20to%20evaluate%20the%20research%20of%20individual%20economics%20faculty%20members%20by%20the%20governing%20body%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20professors%20said%20in%20the%20letter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20professors%20put%20out%20two%20demands%20-%20for%20professor%20Das'%20unconditional%20return%20to%20his%20position%20at%20the%20Ashoka%20University%2C%20and%20for%20the%20governing%20body%20to%20play%20no%20role%20in%20evaluating%20faculty%20research%20through%20any%20committee%20or%20any%20other%20structure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20research%20paper%2C%20Mr%20Das%20stated%20the%20BJP's%20disproportionate%20win%20of%20closely%20contested%20constituencies%20is%20largely%20concentrated%20in%20states%20ruled%20by%20the%20party%20at%20the%20time%20of%20election.%20The%20paper%20said%20the%20density%20of%20the%20incumbent%20party's%20win%20margin%20variable%20exhibited%20a%20discontinuous%20jump%20at%20the%20threshold%20value%20of%20zero.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%2C%20he%20wrote%2C%20implied%20that%20the%20BJP%20won%20disproportionately%20more%20in%20constituencies%20where%20it%20was%20the%20incumbent%20party%20and%20which%20were%20closely%20contested.%20The%20paper%20mainly%20explores%20evidence%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20election%20manipulation%20hypothesis%2C%20also%20arguing%20that%20manipulation%20is%20local%20at%20the%20booth%20level%2C%20and%20implying%20that%20manipulation%20could%20be%20concentrated%20in%20constituencies%20tha