shover%20boss%20can%20also%20hinder%20an%20employee's%20professional%20development.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWorkers%20often%20think%20that%20toxic%20managers%20are%20the%20ones%20that%20are%20the%20most%20overbearing%2C%20but%20sometimes%20a%20laidback%20boss%20can%20be%20more%20damaging%20to%20your%20career.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKevin%20Legg%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Sage%2C%20a%20company%20developing%20training%20and%20curriculums%20for%20workplaces%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F08%2F16%2F3-unexpected-traits-of-bad-bosses-and-tell-tale-signs-of-dysfunction.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20CNBC%20in%20an%20interview%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20one%20of%20the%20most%20unexpected%20traits%20of%20a%20poor%20manager%20is%20actually%20%26quot%3Bundermanaging%26quot%3B%20employees.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20undermanaging%20boss%20falters%20at%20the%20prospect%20of%20making%20difficult%20decisions%20and%20%26quot%3Bwill%20experience%20decision%20paralysis%2C%20making%20a%20bad%20situation%20even%20worse%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20Legg.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELegg%20explained%20that%20undermanagers%20mask%20their%20toxicity%20through%20empty%20goodwill%20gestures.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20make%20matters%20worse%2C%20bad%20bosses%20are%20continually%20making%20a%20virtue%20out%20of%20undermanagement%20%E2%80%A6%20%5Bby%20saying%2C%20for%20example%5D%20'My%20people%20can%20come%20to%20me%20if%20they%20need%20me%20%E2%80%93%20my%20door%20is%20open%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELegg%20says%20that%20this%20type%20of%20manager%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Blazy%20boss%20who%20lacks%20the%20courage%20or%20work%20ethic%20to%20really%20coach%20and%20lead.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20will%20negatively%20impact%20direct%20reports%2C%20especially%20junior%20staffers%20who%20will%20have%20to%20learn%20to%20manage%20themselves.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20medium%20term%2C%20there%20is%20resentment%20at%20annual%20reviews%20when%20folks%20are%20passed%20over%20for%20promotions%20because%20they%20never%20lived%20up%20to%20a%20standard%20they%20were%20never%20shown%2C%26quot%3B%20Legg%20said%20saying%20those%20employees%20eventually%20leave%20for%20managers%20that%20can%20actually%20help%20them%20develop.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInsider's%20%C3%81ine%20Cain%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-your-boss-is-a-pushover-2016-9%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%3Epreviously%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20this%20type%20of%20manager%20is%20actually%20a%20pushover%20boss%20who%20can%20%26quot%3Bseriously%20be%20hurting%20your%20professional%20development.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECain%20said%20the%20characteristics%20of%20a%20pushover%20boss%20include%20indecisiveness%2C%20fleeing%20confrontation%2C%20going%20with%20the%20flow%2C%20and%20letting%20workers%20walk%20all%20over%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20your%20manager%20isn't%20willing%20to%20lead%20you%20toward%20greatness%2C%20that's%20a%20problem%20for%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20Cain%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20good%20for%20your%20professional%20development%20if%20you're%20able%20to%20coast%20by%20with%20mediocre%20work%20for%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPlus%2C%20this%20bad%20attitude%20towards%20leadership%20can%20cause%20your%20workplace%20to%20really%20stagnate%20over%20time.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fundermanaging-basses-as-toxic-as-micromanagers-expert-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692181470000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64dca4554ef9f30019f7e023%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fundermanaging-basses-as-toxic-as-micromanagers-expert-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Employees%20can%20grow%20to%20