C%20Pressing%20for%20'Scientific%20Survey'%20of%20Shahi%20Idgah%20Mosque%20Premises%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F18150906%2FSupreme-Court.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Shri%20Krishna%20Janmabhoomi%20Mukti%20Nirman%20Trust%20in%20Mathura%20has%20moved%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20against%20the%20Allahabad%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20dismissal%20of%20its%20request%20for%20a%20survey%20of%20the%20premises%20of%20the%20Shahi%20Idgah%20mosque%20that%20neighbours%20the%20Mathura%20Shri%20Krishna%20Janmabhoomi%20temple.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Mathura%20mosque%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fkashi-mathura-baaki-hain-why-the-ayodhya-verdict-wont-offer-any-respite-from-saffron-hatred%5C%22%3Eis%20the%20third%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20in%20Ayodhya%20and%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Mosque%20in%20Varanasi%20that%20Hindutva%20organisations%20claim%20are%20illegal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20in%20a%20controversial%20judgment%20allowed%20for%20the%20construction%20of%20a%20Ram%20temple%20at%20the%20disputed%20site%20where%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fayodhyatimeline%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Babri%2520Masjid%2520is%2520constructed%2Cwas%2520the%2520birthplace%2520of%2520Rama.%5C%22%3EHindutva%20activists%20brought%20down%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20in%201992%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20Varanasi%20mosque%20dispute%20has%20heightened%20in%20the%20past%20year%20and%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-greenlights-asi-gyanvapi-survey%5C%22%3Eupheld%20an%20order%20by%20the%20Allahabad%20high%20court%3C%2Fa%3E%20allowing%20the%20Archaeological%20Survey%20of%20India%20to%20conduct%20an%20investigation%20of%20the%20mosque.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Mathura%2C%20the%20Shri%20Krishna%20Janmabhoomi%20Mukti%20Nirman%20Trust%20has%20claimed%20in%20its%20petition%20that%20the%20mosque%20side%20is%20%E2%80%9Cintentionally%20attempting%20to%20seize%20control%20of%20the%20sacred%20worship%20place%2C%20thereby%20preventing%20the%20petitioner%20and%20other%20devoted%20followers%20from%20practicing%20their%20religious%20rituals%20on%20the%20premises%2C%E2%80%9D%20according%20to%20a%20report%20on%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fkrishna-janmabhoomi-trust-supreme-court-premises-survey-8893216%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%20Indian%20Express.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Trust%20in%20its%20petition%20has%20claimed%20that%20the%20Idgah%20mosque%20authorities%20have%20been%20using%20the%20premises%20as%20restrooms%20and%20for%20other%20necessities%20and%20that%20they%20are%20%E2%80%9Ccontinuously%20digging%20and%20destroying%20Hindu%20symbols%2C%20temple%20pillars%2C%20and%20other%20significant%20elements%20of%20the%20temple.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20July%2C%20the%20Allahabad%20high%20court%20had%20dismissed%20its%20application%20for%20a%20%E2%80%9Cscientific%20survey%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20premises%2C%20where%20it%20believes%20the%20mosque%20had%20been%20constructed%20after%20the%20destruction%20of%20a%20temple.%20The%20high%20court%20was%20upholding%20a%20trial%20court%E2%80%99s%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Places%20of%20Worship%20(Special%20Provisions)%20Act%2C%201991%2C%20says%20that%20a%20mosque%2C%20temple%2C%20church%20or%20any%20place%20of%20public%20worship%20in%20existence%20on%20August%2015%201947%2C%20will%20retain%20the%20same%20religious%20character%20that%20it%20had%20on%20that%20day%20%E2%80%93%20irrespective%20of%20its%20history%20%E2%80%93%20and%20cannot%20be%20changed%20by%20the%20courts%20or%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692165643000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F18150906%2FSupreme-Court.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2